-- Persian Gulf Stocks: UNB, Dana Gas, Qatar Electricity & Water
-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 2012-04-23T10:41:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-23/persian-gulf-stocks-unb-dana-gas-qatar-electricity-water.html
Abu Dhabi’s  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  rose
for the first time in three days, gaining 0.1 percent to
2,499.35 at the 2 p.m. close in the United Arab Emirates
capital.  The following shares were active in the Persian Gulf
region. Stock symbols are in parentheses.  Dana Gas PJSC (DANA)   fell 2.1 percent, the most since
March 7, to 46 fils. The company, which has $1 billion in
Islamic bonds due in October, said it will hold a board meeting
on April 25 to discuss project progress.  Qatar Electricity & Water Co. (QEWS QD) rose as much as 1.9
percent to 143.50 riyals before trimming gains to 141.9 riyals.
The Middle East’s second-biggest utility by market
capitalization, said first-quarter profit climbed 28 percent to
291 million riyals ($80 million) after sales rose.  Union National Bank PJSC (UNB)   climbed 2.1 percent, the
most since April 18, to 2.98 dirhams. The bank, whose
shareholders include the  Abu Dhabi  and Dubai governments, said
first-quarter profit rose 3.2 percent to 471.1 million dirhams
($128 million), beating analysts’ estimates.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alaa Shahine in Dubai at 
